<sn><md>### Course Contents

| Topic                                          | Details                                                                                                                                   |
| ---------------------------------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Introduction and Concepts**                  | Nature, types, and distribution of pollutants<br>environmental awareness<br>sources of soil pollution                                     |
| **Key Definitions**                            | PCBs<br>organometallic compounds<br>radioactive materials<br>biomagnification<br>biological half-life                                     |
| **Waste Streams**                              | Sewage sludge<br>industrial effluents<br>hospital and city wastes<br>heavy metal permissible limits                                       |
| **Heavy Metals and Toxins**                    | Arsenic and lead impacts<br>pesticides and fungicides effects<br>soil ecology<br>crop and human health impacts<br>LD50 and biodegradation |
| **Radioactivity**                              | Natural and artificial sources<br>food chain transfer<br>reactor accidents<br>radioactive waste management                                |
| **Waste Management &amp; Bioremediation**          | Waste collection and transportation<br>resource recovery<br>bioremediation techniques<br>atmospheric deposition impacts                   |
| **Industrial Pollution Control in Bangladesh** | Tanning, textile dyeing, fertilizer industries<br>government regulations<br>pollution prevention strategies                               |

</md></sn><sn><md>### Recommended Readings

* The Elements of Environmental Pollution
* Environmental and Pollution Science
* A Handbook on Analysis of Soil, Plant and Water
